  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Characteristics (Different Types) of dizziness</measure>
    <time_frame>6 months</time_frame>
    <description>It will be determined that a patient with dizziness is suffering from what type of Vertigo i.e. Benign Paroxysmal Positional Vertigo, Menier's Disease, Vestibular Neuritis, Labyrinthitis or any other. As these are clinical types of Vertigo these cannot be measured in units</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Quality of Life (QoL) of patients at baselines</measure>
    <time_frame>6 months</time_frame>
    <description>Dizziness Handicap Inventory will be used</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Management of vertigo currently in practice</measure>
    <time_frame>6 months</time_frame>
    <description>As per practice of the physician/Investigator. Management of Vertigo is either by certain maneuvers such as Epley's and Simont or by medications. For the maneuvers, no unit can be defined. The information for medication which will be collected will be Name (preferably the generic name), Dose, Units (form of the medicine), Route and Frequency.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>QoL of patients post treatment</measure>
    <time_frame>6 months</time_frame>
    <description>Dizziness Handicap Inventory will be used</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
